The paper deals with object detection and segmentation using hierarchical structures and convolutional neural networks. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of Locality Sensitive Hashing and automatic hierarchical pruning suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments conducted on the PASCAL VOC 2012 segmentation dataset indicate a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
